snippet: Lawmakers approved the bipartisan budget bill and stronger Pentagon protections for sexual assault victims, but could pass only a one-month extension of the current law involving the farm bill.
abstract: House approves bipartisan budget accord and a Pentagon policy bill that will strengthen protections for victims of sexual assault; adjourns for holiday recess without passing new farm bill, making it likely that Congress will not deal with issue until January.

byline.original: By JONATHAN WEISMAN and JEREMY W. PETERS

lead_paragraph: Lawmakers approved the bipartisan budget bill and stronger Pentagon protections for sexual assault victims, but could pass only a one-month extension of the current law involving the farm bill.

headline.main: House Passes Budget Pact and Military Abuse Protections, but Not Farm Bill
